Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 3;
System.out.println("Result: " + x + y);
```

What is printed when the following code segment runs?

```java
String s = "hello";
s.substring(1, 4);
System.out.println(s);
```

What is the value of `result` after the following code runs?

```java
String word = "programming";
int idx = word.indexOf("gram");
String result = word.substring(idx, idx + 4);
```

What is printed when the following code segment runs?

```java
System.out.print("AP ");
System.out.println("CS");
System.out.print("A");
```

Consider the following code:

```java
String s1 = "hello";
String s2 = new String("hello");
System.out.println(s1.equals(s2));
System.out.println(s1 == s2);
```

What is the output?

What is printed when the following code segment runs?

```java
double x = Math.pow(2, 4);
double y = Math.sqrt(x);
System.out.println((int) y);
```

What is the value of `len` after the following code runs?

```java
String s = "computer science";
int n = s.indexOf("science");
String t = s.substring(0, n - 1);
int len = t.length();
```

A programmer writes the following code to test whether a `String` variable `name` holds `"Alice"`:

```java
if (name == "Alice") {
    System.out.println("Found");
}
```

Which of the following best explains why this code is problematic?

What is printed when the following code runs?

```java
int a = 2;
int b = 3;
System.out.println(a + b + " is the answer");
System.out.println("The answer is " + a + b);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s = "programming";
int idx = s.indexOf("gram");
System.out.println(s.substring(idx, idx + 4));
```

A student writes the following code intending to count the integers stored in `"numbers.txt"`:

```java
File f = new File("numbers.txt");
Scanner sc = new Scanner(f);
int count = 0;
while (f.hasNextInt()) {
    sc.nextInt();
    count++;
}
sc.close();
System.out.println(count);
```

Which of the following identifies the error in this code?

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s = "programming";
System.out.println(s.length());
System.out.println(s.substring(3, 7));
System.out.println(s.indexOf("gram"));
```

Determine the values of `part` and `pos` after the following code runs.

```java
String word = "butterfly";
String part = word.substring(0, 4);
int pos = word.indexOf("fly");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
double x = Math.pow(4, 2);
System.out.println(x);
System.out.println((int) x);
System.out.println(Math.sqrt(x));
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
double x = Math.pow(2, 3);
int y = Math.abs(-5);
double z = Math.sqrt(16);

System.out.print(x + " ");
System.out.print(y + z);
```
